# AI Governance

Canonical source: `context.md`. Do not weaken these rules.

## Invariants

1. Every code change requires `docs/ai/work-items/<feature-id>/`.
2. Pipeline: Architecture → Implementation → Documentation → QA → Code Review → Commit.
3. Failing QA/Review → Implementation; doc gaps → Documenter; BLOCKED → Architecture.
4. Pure reducers only; no side effects in reducers.
5. Features need acceptance criteria, tests, JSDoc, evidence, independent review.
6. Only Committer Agent creates commits (after all gates + commitlint + authorization).
7. Never bypass pipeline for small changes.
8. New dependencies/patterns need documented rationale (ADR when material).
9. Never claim success without executed verification.

## Agents

Read `.ai/agents/<role>.md` for the active stage. Manifest: `.ai/manifest.yml`.

## Entry

New work → Architecture Agent → `01-architecture.md` before any production code.
